{
  "texts": [
    "The notion of Nerve is classical in the algebraic topology literature (see e.g.",
    "[7] chapter 3, section I, example 6, and [3] chapter 5, section 3).",
    "Fact 1.4.2 For every p-site a we have σ a = (κ a) ↓; in other words σ a is the simplicial complex generated by κ a.It follows that σ a is fully determined by κ a.",
    "On the other hand κ a is not determined by σ a.Example A.",
    "As an illustration of the Nerve and the Knit we present two p-sites on the same ground of 6 elements."
  ]
}